3198.Name: "BIG AL" BRASHER MEMORIAL TOURNAMENT - "A" Draw (Saturday)
3198.Details:
The Plan

• Member/Guest tournament organized by Greg Brasher and Chris Johnson and sponsored by the RPTA • "A" Flight to be played on Saturday, April 24th is invitation-only with priority given to players from previous years • One partner must be an RPTA member/the other a non-RPTA member • Play starts at 8am and will end by 5pm • Prizes for winners of the Main Draw, Main Reprieve, Consolation, and Consolation Reprieve • "B" Flight will be played Sunday, April 25th and is open to all RPTA members and their guest

The Logistics

• First 2-3 rounds will be played at either RPTA or CCD courts • Semis and Finals will be played at RPTA • "A" Draw will be set by Greg Brasher and Chris Johnson using advanced analytics, AI, computer algorithms, machine learning, and wind direction • Pro paddle tourney bracket (main draw, main reprieve, consolation, and consolation reprieve) with byes for the seeds • All matches up to the Finals will be 2 full sets with a 3rd set played as a 10-point tie breaker • Finals will be 3 full sets with 7-point tiebreaker at 6-6 • Each team will play at least three matches • Light breakfast, lunch, beer, and beverages will be served

The Cost

• $95 per person / $190 per team • Your registration isn't complete until you've paid • You must register and pay for both players at the same time • Registration fee includes a tournament-branded vest • Include size information for Tournament Vest for both you and your partner and contact information for your partner • "A" Draw code required for registration

Thank Yous

• RPTA for setting aside the court time and hosting the tournament • Country Club of Darien for allowing us to use their courts • "Big Al" Brasher for inspiring the tournament, its camaraderie, and its competition TO REGISTER ClICK ON "REGISTER" LINK AT TOP OF PAGE

3583.Name: "BIG AL" BRASHER MEMBER/GUEST TOURNAMENT - "A" Draw (Apr 9)
3583.Details:
The Plan

• 17th Annual Member/Guest tournament organized by Greg Brasher and Chris Johnson and sponsored by the RPTA • "A" Draw tournament will be played Sunday, April 10th • "A" Draw is by invite-only with first priority given to players from prior years and then to top Rowayton players as determined by the Tournament Directors • One partner of each team must be an RPTA member and the other a non-RPTA member - teams with two RPTA members are highly discouraged and require Tournament Director approval • Prizes for winners of the Main Draw, Main Reprieve, Consolation, and Consolation Reprieve • "B" Draw tournament will be played Sunday, April 10th

The Logistics

• Play starts at 8am and the finals should end by 5pm • Each team will play at least three matches • Pro paddle tourney bracket (main draw, main reprieve, consolation, and consolation reprieve) with byes for the top seeds • First 2-3 rounds will be played at either RPTA or another club's courts (TBD) • Semis and Finals will be played at RPTA • The draw will be set by Greg Brasher and Chris Johnson using advanced analytics, AI, computer algorithms, machine learning, and wind direction • All matches up to the Finals will be 2 full sets with 7-point tiebreaker at 6-6 and a 3rd set played as a 10-point tiebreaker, if needed • Finals will be 3 full sets with 7-point tiebreaker at 6-6 • Light breakfast, lunch, beer, and beverages will be served

The Cost

• $100 per person / $200 per team • You must register and pay for both players and give your partner's name and contact information at the same time - your registration isn't complete until you've concluded the PayPal payment • Registration fee includes a tournament-branded pair of shorts - you must include size information for tournament shorts for both you and your partner when registering • No refunds unless a suitable replacement team is found • Rain date is April 30th

Thank Yous

• RPTA for setting aside the court time • "Big Al" Brasher for inspiring the tournament, its camaraderie, and its competition
